d for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Digery Dickery Carwithen was born in 1560, in England, his father, Richard Carwithen, was 23 and his mother, Elizabeth Dyrant, was 22. He had at least 1 son with Maria “Mary” Biewett."},"et":{"Cir 1560–":"1560–Surnud","1560–Male":"1560–Surnud","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1565–Female":"1565–Surnud","1537–1637":"1537–1637","1538–1580":"1538–1580","about 1590":"umbes 1590","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1590":"1590","Cir 1560":"1560","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1665":"1665","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1565":"1565","1651":"1651","1538":"1538","1637":"1637","1537":"1537","England":"England"},"fi":{"Cir 1560–":"1560–Kuollut","1560–Male":"1560–Kuollut","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1565–Female":"1565–Kuollut","1537–1637":"1537–1637","1538–1580":"1538–1580","about 1590":"noin 1590","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1590":"1590","Cir 1560":"1560","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1665":"1665","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1565":"1565","1651":"1651","1538":"1538","1637":"1637","1537":"1537","England":"England"},"fr":{"Cir 1560–":"1560–Décédé","1560–Male":"1560–Décédé","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1565–Female":"1565–Décédée","1537–1637":"1537–1637","1538–1580":"1538–1580","about 1590":"environ 1590","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1590":"1590","Cir 1560":"1560","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","1665":"1665","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1565":"1565","1651":"1651","1538":"1538","1637":"1637","1537":"1537","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Digery Dickery Carwithen est né en 1560, à Angleterre, son père, Richard Carwithen, avait 23 ans et sa mère, Elizabeth Dyrant, avait 22 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Maria “Mary” Biewett."},"de":{"Cir 1560–":"1560–Verstorben","1560–Male":"1560–Verstorben","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1565–Female":"1565–Verstorben","1537–1637":"1537–1637","1538–1580":"1538–1580","ab